I have a Mac - the product works some of the time, but with frequent disconnects it's not worth the effort. On the host Mac side the software gets stuck and the only way to attempt a reconnect is to quit it completely.  The vendor claims that you can connect to your device with an ad-hoc wifi network, but doesn't explain that it only works for Windows computers and that most Android devices cannot see adhoc networks without being rooted. Ad-hoc on Macs is very insecure.   I wish this was more stable, because when it does work its a great way to gain some extra screen real estate.  I'm going to ask for a refund.
